Source: Growth and Development of Social Security
Author:
Vol / Page: 19
Edition:
Quote: The term `social security' has passed into the political vocabulary of the English-speaking world, and the ideal of social security is now accepted by almost all democratic governments. The problem of bringing about social security has a different background in different countries and is being solved by different methods. It is clear also that the term `social security' means somewhat different things in different countries. In the following chapters, therefore, an attempt has been made to explain and demonstrate what `social security' means as applied to New Zealand, and the progress that has been made over the years to make that ideal a reality.
